survey_response.review_text: I have been visiting the Doctor from about 8 years. It started with high Gestational diabetics but eventually I got to know that I am type -2 diabetic. I have delivered two babies through normal delivery under her guidance. She is so supportive with me through out this 8 yrs giving encouragement and support and lead me in proper direction in controlling diabetics. When I am not caring for myself and taking care of kids more, she made me understand how important is mothers health to take care of baby and brought me back in track. She visited me personally to check how I am doing in the delivery room. This means a lot to me. She did not restrict to just giving me medicines. She treated me as a child. For me she is walking GOD. Without her proper direction I couldn't deliver my kids safely and with proper health.

Dr Sumathi is a lovely person with absolute knowledge n very very approachable. 
Gives thorough explanation of Wat is required to be done makes the patient self sufficient 

She boosts their confidence n gives them comfort. M a big fan of her methods to control n manage diabetes
She patiently went thru all my records. And explained my illness. Gave me a lot of confidence. A very positive doctor and does not scare u  as most of them do now.
She is so cool and explain very clearly about diet and how to control sugar levels. She is very experienced and nice doctor
Good explanation provided not in hurry very pleasing to talk and motivates patients . smiling face and very polite
*** **** *************** ** ***** We go and and visit her even though the hospital is quite far from our home. Very patient and encouraging doctor
Excellent is the word, we were very happy. She was very patient diligent n explained us in detail....

Wonderful!! She was the one whom I needed at this point of time. Very positive approach and always makes me feel good and gets me out of depression. Gets a lot of confidence in me.I recommend her 101% for all the pregnant ladies out there!!
